  "text": "In fact, a bigger class of seasonal models contains ARIMA models [CITATION_1] . The linear ARIMA models and feed forward artificial neural networks (FFANN) were studied [CITATION_2] . It was found that from the minimization of the assessment set error in the ARIMA process the model arrangement is chosen. Multi-step forecasting and the consequent averaging to produce mean hourly predictions of wind statistics was suggested by them. [CITATION_3] extensively studied the ARIMA models. They equally considered non-seasonal and seasonal ARIMA models by using stochastic parts. They also decided to calculate the perseverance patterns if any, of the stochastic components.",
